-- Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, Credicorp, Minsur, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-06-06T21:21:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/peru-stocks-candente-casa-grande-credicorp-minsur.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trading.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 1.8 percent to 21,018.91. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 2.5 percent to 2,717.21.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose 4.4 percent to 2.58 soles after tin advanced in
 London .  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, gained 3.1 percent to $29.60 after copper jumped in
 New York , said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, climbed 3.1 percent to 66 cents.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, advanced 3.4 percent to 13.60 soles
after sugar rose in New York.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, gained 3 percent to $121 after Itau BBA Securities
analyst Nicolas Chialva rated the stock a new “Outperform.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
